<br>
The best places to reliablly farm platinum are Sebilis (guard area gems, Jugg's, reets, and Crypt for valuable spells), Hill giants in Rathe, Ice Giants in EverFrost, and the Guards in Felwithe.  The Felwithe guards are all Paladins that drop up to 6 pp, sometimes a gem or Fine Steel weapon, and they ALWAYS drop a 2 handed sword which sells for up to 21 pp with +Cha gear.  I farmed Felwithe for the platinum that paid for my Selo's speed Drogmor.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
<br>
If you quad-kite, you could quad Wyverns in CS for hides/gems, Suits of Armor in WL for Velious quest gems/Blood Ember armor, or the Coldains in EW (the ones with no faction hit) for Coldain heads and their Fine Steel.<br>
<br>
You could also try getting a group of friends together that don't mind all-out treasure hunting, and go hunt places where you can aquire droppable items to sell.  If your they are close friends you can throw the items you farm up on a Bazaar mule and split the profits amongst the crew.<br>
<br>
